The paper focuses on visual recognition tasks and proposes a framework that utilizes convolutional neural network models for feature extraction. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques and context-aware algorithms, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its proposed framework on standard benchmarks for image classification (cs.MM) and visual instance retrieval (cs.IR), indicating that these sub-categories are also relevant.
